            "body": "With https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/48e2a73610ca5639408f79b3d8eebd3e5f57a327 handling scheduled events during the prompt, a scheduled `foldUpdate()` from the foldexpr somehow breaks the highlighter.\n\n\nThis patch prevents the issue but maybe there is a way to make the highlighter less fragile against outside interference?\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/input.c b/src/nvim/input.c\nindex ca2a13e016..3aed20a9a4 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/input.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/input.c\n@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@\n \n #include \"nvim/ascii_defs.h\"\n #include \"nvim/ex_getln.h\"\n+#include \"nvim/fold.h\"\n #include \"nvim/getchar.h\"\n #include \"nvim/gettext_defs.h\"\n #include \"nvim/globals.h\"\n@@ -170,10 +171,12 @@ int prompt_for_input(char *prompt, int hl_id, bool one_key, bool *mouse_used)\n \n   no_mapping++;  // don't map prompt input\n   allow_keys++;  // allow special keys\n+  disable_fold_update++;\n   char *resp = getcmdline_prompt(-1, prompt, hl_id, EXPAND_NOTHING, NULL,\n                                  CALLBACK_NONE, one_key, mouse_used);\n   allow_keys--;\n   no_mapping--;\n+  disable_fold_update--;\n \n   if (resp) {\n     ret = one_key ? (int)(*resp) : atoi(resp);\n```",
